   African Americans demonstrate increased obsessions and compulsions in relation to racial everyday discrimination, but not in relation to nonracial everyday discrimination. These findings suggest that policymakers should consider the unique negative impact of racial discrimination on the mental health of African Americans, in addition to other forms of discrimination that they may face.
